metadata.name: The Song Of Colors #11
metadata.description:
Watercolor painting was my favorite technique for playing. I love combining colors, merging and blending them together. Furthermore, I started experimenting with large pieces of canvas, placed them at different heights, and poured vast layers of acrylic fluid paint on them.
The energy of these paintings is incredible. As I layer the colors, the colors begin to converse. It seems to have the color of its own mind.
I started with an image in mind, but always, painting takes over everything. Using canvas installed at different heights requires careful thinking and planning in advance. Sometimes the color goes into a new shape that I did not expect, but I correct it and use it to the fullest. This kind of art creates exciting and psychological paintings!
Color flow is instantaneous. I am constantly spinning around the canvas and directing the flow; there is no time but to go with the flow. I started as a guide, but I know that I've just been an active agent - letting the song of colors sing and flow.
- Press "S" to save an artwork.

Made with p5js.

metadata.name: Glomularus #127
metadata.description:
Glomularus is an exploration in generative, artificial life forms. The project is an extension of my Protobyte series, begun in 2004.

Driven by Verlet icosahedra and responsive tendrils, Glomulari live in a spherical virtual ecosystem (V-eco) enhanced through user interaction.

Interaction:

Mouse/Trackpad:
  drag -> camera rotation
  drag + CMD/CTR -> camera pan
  scroll wheel/pinch -> camera zoom

Key Input:
  1-9: add acceleration
  -, +: reduce | increase V-eco sphere radius
  f, g: reduce | increase fog
  p: screen capture

Tip:
To decrease creature acceleration, reduce V-eco sphere radius

Note:
Please post your favorite Glomularus screen captures
TW: @iragreenberg
IG: @greenberg.ira

Built with Three.js, PByte.js, TypeScript, Node

metadata.name: pico_cascades #209
metadata.description:
A Pico-8 demake of my Entropy series previously made on the TIC-80. Due to many of the limitations baked into the Pico-8, this version lacks many of the features from the TIC-80 version, as well having a lower speed, and lower resolution. However, it also has some new features, like mirroring, that provide an interesting twist. fxhash Features are enabled in order to track rarity, there are some rare features like mirror type, or brush_wiggle (which decreases the stability of the visual equilibrium).

This piece is build on the `aebrer_engine` codebase I have developed for Pico-8.

creator: Andrew E. Brereton
date: 2021-11-15
twitter: @aebrer
website: aebrer.xyz
platform: Pico-8, Lua

metadata.name: Acid Drops #151
metadata.description:
Acid Drops is an algorithm that generates drops of LSD.  Each drop contains a colorful, silly, sometimes-scary little psychedelic world that is waiting to unfurl.  The drops are all spheres of exactly the same size, but each one dances around differently and refracts glimpses of a future psychedelic colorscape.

Created by @capnganj - one love <3

metadata.name: TV Test-Blocks #6
metadata.description: These TV test blocks generated from my base experimental code named "Mind Blocks" on Processing4. The TV test patterns is widely recognized as one of the iconic populer culture symbols of the 1980s and 1990s. Numerous novelty and collectible items has been patterned after the famous test card, including wall clocks, badseets, wristwatches, and clothing (wiki says). So why shouldn't they find a place for themselves as generative token?

metadata.name: Mount Doodle #326
metadata.description:
Tried my best to make every doodle aesthetically pleasing to the eyes.
However, just like nature, beauty often lies in imperfections. :)

Made with p5.js.
Primary split 5% with The Processing Foundation.

Keys
- 1: view 1000px png (Default)
- 2: download 2000px png
- 4: download 4000px png
- 8: download 8000px png
- s: save the image as PNG

When downloading higher resolution pngs, it might take several seconds to redraw the whole image. Download will start immediately after redrawing is completed. Please bear with the slow rendering.
